","about 1198":"about 1198","about 1196":"about 1196","1219":"1219","Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom":"Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom","Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckinghamshire, England","Hanslope, Buckinghamshire, England":"Hanslope, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom","England":"England","Stourton,Mere,Wiltshire,England":"Stourton, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Mauduit","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["Norman, English:  see  Mawditt  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Mawditt","meanings":["Norman, English: nickname from Old French  <i>mal-duit</i> ‘badly brought up, ill educated’ (Latin  <i>male doctus</i>)."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert Mauduit Lord of Hanslope was born about 1171, in Hanslope, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, William Mauduit Baron of Hanslope, was 28 and his mother, Isabel Hedwig St Liz, was 38. He married Isabella Basset about 1190, in Hanslope, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter. He died on 2 June 1221, in his hometown, at the age of 51."},"et":{"about 1171–2 Jun 1221":"umbes 1171–2. juuni 1221","1171–1221":"1171–1221","1172–1224":"1172–1224","1195–1219":"1195–1219","1196–1257":"1196–1257","1198–Male":"1198–Surnud","1144–1194":"1144–1194","1135–1171":"1135–1171","about 1171":"umbes 1171","about 1190":"umbes 1190","1198":"1198","1196":"1196","1195":"1195","1194":"1194","1172":"1172","1171":"1171","1160":"1160","2 Jun 1221":"2. juuni 1221","1257":"1257","1224":"1224","1135":"1135","1144":"1144","1221":"1221","2 October 1194":"2. oktoober 1194","about 1198":"umbes 1198","about 1196":"umbes 1196","1219":"1219","Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom":"Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckinghamshire, England","Hanslope, Buckinghamshire, England":"Hanslope, Buckinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","Stourton,Mere,Wiltshire,England":"Stourton, Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1171–2 Jun 1221":"noin 1171–2. kesäkuuta 1221","1171–1221":"1171–1221","1172–1224":"1172–1224","1195–1219":"1195–1219","1196–1257":"1196–1257","1198–Male":"1198–Kuollut","1144–1194":"1144–1194","1135–1171":"1135–1171","about 1171":"noin 1171","about 1190":"noin 1190","1198":"1198","1196":"1196","1195":"1195","1194":"1194","1172":"1172","1171":"1171","1160":"1160","2 Jun 1221":"2. kesäkuuta 1221","1257":"1257","1224":"1224","1135":"1135","1144":"1144","1221":"1221","2 October 1194":"2. lokakuuta 1194","about 1198":"noin 1198","about 1196":"noin 1196","1219":"1219","Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom":"Wiltshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckinghamshire, England","Hanslope, Buckinghamshire, England":"Hanslope, Buckinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"England","Stourton,Mere,Wiltshire,England":"Stourton, Wiltshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1171–2 Jun 1221":"environ 1171–2 juin 1221","1171–1221":"1171–1221","1172–1224":"1172–1224","1195–1219":"1195–1219","1196–1257":"1196–1257","1198–Male":"1198–Décédé","1144–1194":"1144–1194","1135–1171":"1135–1171","about 1171":"environ 1171","about 1190":"environ 1190","1198":"1198","1196":"1196","1195":"1195","1194":"1194","1172":"1172","1171":"1171","1160":"1160","2 Jun 1221":"2 juin 1221","1257":"1257","1224":"1224","1135":"1135","1144":"1144","1221":"1221","2 October 1194":"2 octobre 1194","about 1198":"environ 1198","about 1196":"environ 1196","1219":"1219","Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom":"Wiltshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckinghamshire, Angleterre","Hanslope, Buckinghamshire, England":"Hanslope, Buckinghamshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","England":"Angleterre","Stourton,Mere,Wiltshire,England":"Stourton, Wiltshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Robert Mauduit Lord of Hanslope est né environ 1171, à Hanslope, Buckinghamshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, son père, William Mauduit Baron of Hanslope, avait 28 ans et sa mère, Isabel Hedwig St Liz, avait 38 ans. Il a épousé Isabella Basset environ 1190, à Hanslope, Buckinghamshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Ils ont eu au moins 2 fils et 1 fille. Il est décédé le 2 juin 1221, dans sa ville natale, à l’âge de 51 ans."},"de":{"about 1171–2 Jun 1221":"um 1171–2. Juni 1221","1171–1221":"1171–1221","1172–1224":"1172–1224","1195–1219":"1195–1219","1196–1257":"1196–1257","1198–Male":"1198–Verstorben","1144–1194":"1144–1194","1135–1171":"1135–1171","about 1171":"um 1171","about 1190":"um 1190","1198":"1198","1196":"1196","1195":"1195","1194":"1194","1172":"1172","1171":"1171","1160":"1160","2 Jun 1221":"2. Juni 1221","1257":"1257","1224":"1224","1135":"1135","1144":"1144","1221":"1221","2 October 1194":"2. Oktober 1194","about 1198":"um 1198","about 1196":"um 1196","1219":"1219","Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom":"Wil